00:44:06,320 --> 00:44:08,200
Stupid.

358
00:44:48,520 --> 00:44:50,400
Go check it out!

359
00:44:58,240 --> 00:45:00,880
It's the coroner from China station!

360
00:45:05,320 --> 00:45:07,200
He didn't stand a chance.

361
00:45:12,080 --> 00:45:13,960
It's Virgil!

362
00:45:14,000 --> 00:45:15,525
Who dunnit?  

363
00:45:15,560 --> 00:45:17,400
Who dunnit?  
 - Clayton Young.

364
00:45:36,000 --> 00:45:37,880
Aww, to hell with it!

365
00:45:38,560 --> 00:45:40,440
Come on you guys!

366
00:45:40,475 --> 00:45:41,920
Matt!

367
00:45:42,000 --> 00:45:43,405
You ain't finished!  

368
00:45:43,440 --> 00:45:46,560
You ain't finished!  
 - He ain't going anywhere.

369
00:45:50,760 --> 00:45:52,640
Sorry.

370
00:46:08,480 --> 00:46:11,320
What are my choices?

371
00:46:12,720 --> 00:46:14,600
You could teach in a school.

372
00:46:16,560 --> 00:46:19,560
Or I do know a whorehouse you could work at.

373
00:46:19,880 --> 00:46:22,840
Or I could get married again!

374
00:46:31,320 --> 00:46:36,200
I think it's better not to rely on people or things  
 you can lose.

375
00:46:36,600 --> 00:46:39,040
You never needed anyone?

376
00:46:39,240 --> 00:46:43,400
No. And I prefer to keep it that way.

377
00:46:45,480 --> 00:46:50,680
So you're telling me, you don't need me tonight?

378
00:46:55,120 --> 00:46:59,040
Well... The nights do get cold up in these parts...

379
00:47:02,320 --> 00:47:04,200
Looks like they cleared out.

380
00:47:04,280 --> 00:47:07,600
Yeah... but not before getting to know each other real well!

381
00:47:19,120 --> 00:47:24,320
Take it easy on him, willya?  
 I've never seen him upset like that.

382
00:47:26,320 --> 00:47:29,960
They might already be in Liberty!

383
00:47:38,720 --> 00:47:42,600
It's better if we're not seen together.  
 You go to the hotel!

384
00:47:42,800 --> 00:47:44,520
On foot?!?

385
00:47:53,800 --> 00:47:55,960
Have a nice walk!

386
00:48:11,720 --> 00:48:14,920
Didn't I tell you I didn't want to be - - -

387
00:48:15,080 --> 00:48:18,480
Oh, Mister Young!

388
00:48:20,400 --> 00:48:23,245
Your punctuality matches your reputation.  

389
00:48:23,280 --> 00:48:25,720
Your punctuality matches your reputation.  
 - Saberneck's dead, where's my money?

390
00:48:26,080 --> 00:48:31,120
Since you killed my scout, I would need some proof.

391
00:48:36,320 --> 00:48:38,525
I got his rifle.  

392
00:48:38,560 --> 00:48:39,960
I got his rifle.  
 - Not good enough.

393
00:48:41,320 --> 00:48:43,560
The girl?

394
00:48:43,960 --> 00:48:47,600
She wasn't part of the deal.

395
00:48:47,960 --> 00:48:53,720
I'll send someone to check on Saberneck.  
 Come back again here tomorrow.

396
00:48:55,000 --> 00:48:58,640
You better have my money ready.

397
00:49:00,480 --> 00:49:04,200
Chapter 11:  
 Dead Man Walking

398
00:49:21,520 --> 00:49:24,960
This damn thing!  
 - Damn!

399
00:49:25,040 --> 00:49:28,680
Pull up over at the pond! Hey Duke!  
 Pull up over at the pond!

400
00:49:33,200 --> 00:49:36,520
Gimme the water bottle.

401
00:50:07,160 --> 00:50:10,800
Ain't you gonna save your bullets for that whore?

402
00:50:21,880 --> 00:50:23,565
Everything okay?  

403
00:50:23,600 --> 00:50:25,360
Everything okay?  
 - He's gone crazy.

404
00:50:25,520 --> 00:50:29,160
Yeah, probably.

405
00:51:05,200 --> 00:51:08,840
Spread out! Be careful, it could be a trap.

406
00:51:52,160 --> 00:51:55,240
What are you doing? The wind is coming from the east!

407
00:51:55,440 --> 00:51:57,645
Are you saying I should've smelled her?  

408
00:51:57,680 --> 00:51:59,080
Are you saying I should've smelled her?  
 - I did.

409
00:52:15,680 --> 00:52:20,280
I hope you don't mind...  
 I ordered for you.

410
00:52:32,320 --> 00:52:35,960
So... Where are we going tomorrow?

411
00:52:53,520 --> 00:52:57,240
Chapter 12:  
 Ways Of Honor

412
00:53:18,040 --> 00:53:20,445
Your bus leaves in the morning.  

413
00:53:20,480 --> 00:53:22,280
Your bus leaves in the morning.  
- But I want to go with you.

414
00:53:25,160 --> 00:53:26,005
Wouldn't work.  

415
00:53:26,040 --> 00:53:28,800
Wouldn't work.  
 - Why not?

416
